# Component Conventions

- Functional components only. No class components.
- Define Props interface above the component, named `{ComponentName}Props`.
- Use named exports: `export function MyComponent() {}`, not default exports.
- Colocate test file next to component: `Button.tsx` + `Button.test.tsx`.
- Extract custom hooks when logic is reused or component gets complex.
- Prefer composition over prop drilling — use context or compound components.
- All event handlers prefixed with `handle`: `handleClick`, `handleSubmit`.
- Memoize expensive computations with `useMemo`, callbacks with `useCallback`.
- Always handle loading, error, and empty states explicitly.
- Components under 200 lines — split if larger.
